{
  "texts": [
    "The network design principle (paradigm) is shifting from connection-centric to data-centric (Yan et al., 2021).",
    "These two planes are thus not applicable to data-driven services for the following reasons:",
    "Data derived from 6G networks are abundant and expensive for the current control plane, e.g., an SBI that features reliable transport of small data packets and short-term connections.",
    "Data topologies of emerging 6G services have become complicated with diverse producers and consumers, including RAN nodes, UE, and NFs, which are no longer connected in a simple point-to-point manner.",
    "Data aggregation, fusion, and distribution are commonly used in data topologies."
  ]
}